26/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Humanitarian Law Centre (FHP) has filed a criminal complaint against five former police and army officers for war crimes allegedly committed against Albanians in the Pec municipality in 1998 and 1999, local media reported on Wednesday (August 25th).
The complaint was submitted to Serbia's war crimes prosecutor's office.
The FHP argues that the five are responsible for killing 49 ethnic Albanians, destruction of Albanian homes, torture, intimidation and persecution of Albanians from villages in Pec.
(Tanjug, B92, RTS - 25/08/10)
